<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Draper</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Italy and Greece only countries so far as known requiring consular visé.
                            It is the discrimination of Italy in requiring visé for meats from
                            United States to which this Government particularly objects.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>